Pronotum cordiform (Fig. 1), longer (0.60 mm) than wide (0.51-0.27 mm), maximum width (0.51 mm) close to anterior angles, almost double minimum width (0.27 
mm
), at the posterior angles. Anterior angles obtuse, rounded. Anterior margin regularly convex. Median line apparent, marked with two depressions. Two lateral setae at anterior and posterior angles. Lateral margin sinuate before posterior angles.
